<p>
  <span class="nym">Berengaria</span>
  <span class="gen">f.</span>
  
  <span class="etym"><span class="lang">Old High German, Old Saxon</span> <i>bero</i> 'bear' + <span class="lang">Old High German, Old Saxon</span> <i>gēr</i> 'spear'.
  </span>
  
</p>
  
<div class="usg">
  <p>The name of a 12th C queen consort of Castile, a 12th C queen consort of England, a 12th/13th C queen consort of Castile and Leon, a 13th C empress consort of Constantinople, and a 13th C queen consort of Denmark.</p>
</div>
  
  
<div class="def">
  <p>Fem. of <a class="nym" href="Berengar">Berengar</a>.</p>
  
  


